3 hours) See the tracksheet for more details. For previous catalog year requirements, access the catalog archive. BS in Aviation Logistics (120 hours) University Core Curriculum Components (42 hours) See BBA Requirements Pre-Business Requirements (15-24 hours) See BBA Requirements Upper Level Business Foundation Requirements (15 hours) BLAW 3430: Legal and Ethical Environment of Business BCIS 3610: Basic Information Systems MKTG 3650: Marketing Foundations FINA 3770: Finance MGMT 3720: Organizational Behavior Professional Field and Supporting Courses (39 hours) See the tracksheet for more details. BS/MS in Accounting (150 hours) University Core Curriculum Components (42 hours) See BBA Requirements Pre-Business Requirements (20-24 hours) Minimum grade of "C" is required in all pre-business courses. Economics (6 hours) ECON 1100 Microeconomics ECON 1110 Macroeconomics Mathematics (3 hours) 3 hours from MATH 1190 or1710 Free Electives: Number of required free elective hours will vary depending on course selection and/or placement. Students must complete a minimum of 120 hours for BS in Accounting Control Systems degree or a minimum of 114 hours for the BS/MS in Accounting undergraduate portion of the degree. Business Computer Information Systems (3 hours) BCIS 2610 Accounting (6 hours) ACCT 2010 Principles of Accounting (Financial Accounting) ACCT 2020 Principles of Accounting (Managerial Accounting) Data Analysis with Spreadsheets (3 hours) Minimum grade of "C" required. DSCI 2710 Upper Level Business Foundation Requirements (18 hours) BLAW 3430: Legal and Ethical Environment of Business BCIS 3610: Basic Information Systems MKTG 3650: Marketing Foundations FINA 3770: Finance MGMT 3720: Organizational Behavior DSCI 3710: Business Statistical Analysis Using Spreadsheets Professional Field and Supporting Courses (31-40 hours) See the undergraduate catalog , or the BS in Accounting tracksheets for the required courses. Visit the Department of Accounting website for more information. For previous catalog year requirements, access the catalog archive. Physical Address: University of North Texas College of Business 1307 West Highland Street Denton, Texas 76201 Contact the College of Business Mailing Address: University of North Texas College of Business 1155 Union Circle #311160 Denton, TX 76203-5017 Contact the College of Business This Website: © 2017 UNT College of Business For issues or comments related to this website, please contact us.   Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy | Web Accessibility | State of Texas Online | Emergency Preparedness | THECB Online Resume System 